This software was developed for academic research and educational purposes only.
It is not intended, designed, tested, certified, or approved for clinical use,
medical diagnosis, treatment planning, or any other medical application.

The outputs produced by this system — including but not limited to class
predictions, confidence scores, Grad-CAM overlays, LIME explanations, and SHAP
attribution maps — are experimental results generated by a machine learning
model trained on a publicly available dataset. They do not constitute medical
advice, clinical opinion, or diagnostic conclusions.

The authors make no warranties, express or implied, regarding the accuracy,
reliability, completeness, or clinical validity of the system's outputs.
Brain tumor diagnosis is a complex clinical task requiring comprehensive
evaluation by qualified and licensed medical professionals, including but not
limited to neuroradiologists, neurologists, and neurosurgeons.

Any use of this software in a clinical or patient-facing context, without
appropriate regulatory approval (e.g., FDA 510(k), CE Mark, or equivalent),
is strictly prohibited and is the sole responsibility of the user.

